.TH "igc_io_error_detected" 9 "igc_io_error_detected" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
igc_io_error_detected \- called when PCI error is detected
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "pci_ers_result_t" igc_io_error_detected
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "pci_channel_state_t state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
Pointer to PCI device
.IP "state" 12
The current PCI connection state

This function is called after a PCI bus error affecting
this device has been detected.
